# Container Runtime Detection

- Do not assume Docker is the available container runtime in this repo.
- Before container-dependent verification or local stack commands, check both `docker` and `podman`.
- If Docker is unavailable but Podman is available, use Podman instead of stopping on a false blocker.
- For compose-style commands, check both `docker compose` and `podman compose`; prefer the runtime that exists on this machine.
- When a local CI or release workflow mentions Docker-based validation, adapt it to the available runtime rather than skipping the step.
- When checking whether a required local service exists, inspect existing Podman containers before starting a duplicate one.
